The woman had a legal claim against the husband or his paterfamilias to a donatio propter nuptias equivalent to the dos she brought herself. During the continuance of the marriage it was under the control οἱ the husband, and in fact belonged to him, but he could not alienate land or houses comprised in it even with the con- sent of the wife, who had a statutory hypothec over all his property to secure its delivery should she become entitled. ln case of her death, or divorce through her fault, it ceased to have any further legal existence; il the marriage terminated through the husband's death or divorce oc· casioned by him, she had no claim upon it, unless there was issue, save by express agreemeut; il there was issue, she was entitled to the usufruct3 the dominium she shared with the children.
